This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as duplicate detection and dialogue act tagging, which are typically categorized under the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses word embeddings, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) tasks. Additionally, the paper involves classification tasks, which are a core component of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with document-level embeddings, which are relevant to the subfield of social and information networks (cs.SI).
